plot: Grey gives Tim and Lucy an unromantic assignment, while John and Celina track down a missing girl. Multiple relationships come to a head at a charity gala.

It's Valentine's Day and the cops are looking forward to a charity gala organized by West's wife. Nolan asks Bailey if she helped Malvado take out Jason. And she chooses not to answer. Nolan and Suarez respond to a call wherein a man is Ara king a woman. Once they get the man to calm down they learn he's from Mexico and he's looking for his daughter who came to L.A. to find work. The woman hired the daughter but doesn't know where she is. Nolan and Suarez promise to do what they can to find her. They track the daughter's movement and discover she was at the apartment of a known Russian criminal. They check it out but don't find her. At the gala some unlikely couples hook up. The father shows and demanding why are they not looking for his daughter. The next day Suarez has a theory which she takes to Nolan and they pursue it.—Rcs0411@yahoo.com
